{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place peanuts in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Rinse mixing bowl and make dressing.","Stir lime juice, palm sugar, chilli, fish sauce and pepper together in a bowl then set aside and continue with recipe.","Place ginger, 60 g onions and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add water and heat <nobr>10 min\/80°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Insert simmering basket. Add chicken then cook <nobr>25-30 min\/80°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Leave chicken to cool, then cover and refrigerate. Empty mixing bowl.","Place 60 g onion slices in a bowl and cover with cold water. Leave to soak in fridge for 15 minutes, then drain.","Soak noodles in hot water until soft and they come apart easily (approx. 10-15 minutes).  Drain noodles through Varoma dish, rinse in cold water and drain again. Place drained noodles on a board and cut through a few times with a sharp knife.","Once chicken has cooled, place chicken in mixing bowl and shred <nobr>5-7 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. The chicken should be in pieces approx. 6 cm x 1.5 cm. Transfer to a bowl, dress with half the reserved dressing, add reserved onion slices, mint and coriander. Toss lightly to combine and add more dressing to taste.","Arrange noodles on a serving plateand pile chicken salad on top, working the chicken through the noodles with fingers.  Scatter with reserved chopped peanuts to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g peanuts, roasted, unsalted","4 limes, juice only","3 tsp palm sugar","1 fresh chilli, thinly sliced","1 Tbsp fish sauce","1 tsp ground black pepper","30 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","60 g onions, quartered","2 garlic cloves","1600 g water, plus extra for soaking","700 g chicken breasts, boneless and skinless, halved on the grain","60 g onions, thinly sliced","water, cold, for soaking","200 g dried rice noodles","water, hot, for soaking","15 g fresh mint leaves","½ bunch fresh coriander leaves"]}],"id":"r238755","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-y-X-EVoF-t8\/XZQGHGbdImI\/AAAAAAAAb6U\/qDxZfwQfB5MEWArUbMVcr7xIFHMEN_wbgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ICwroLZsUYvpOh8f.png","title":"Indochine Chicken Salad","publishedAt":"2018-03-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"42 g","fat":"25 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"29 g","calories":"2096 kJ \/ 501 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sharp knife, serving plate, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["The chicken can be cooked a day in advance and placed in the fridge.","Chicken stock can be used to poach the chicken instead of water.","Any leftover chicken can be tossed with some dressing for a classic sandwich."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 20m","4 portions"]}